  "text": "Drinking of milk appeared to produce indirect activation of K receptors, through dopamine mediation, because the decrease by milk in rat fetal facial wiping to a tactile probe was inhibited by nor-binaltorphimine or the D~ antagonist SCH-23390. Either U50,488 or the D1 agonist SKF-38393 mimicked milk's effect of reduced wiping responses, and these actions were blocked by the appropriate antagonist [CITATION_1] . Intake of sucrose lowered concentrations of 3-endorphin in the dorsal, but not ventral, hypothalamus in spontaneously hypertensive rats, but not in normal rats [CITATION_2] , so that the endogenous opiate system was activated by the sucrose in a specialized population.",
